<p class="g-mb-30">The Vadtal Swaminarayan Temple is a masterpiece in itself. The temple is a lotus shape when viewed from the top &amp; has 9 domes. Higher number domes were considered very impressive, especially during the time, the temple was built. Vadtal temple having 9 domes tell a lot about the impressiveness of the construction.</p>
<p class="g-mb-30">Also known as Lakshminarayan Dev Gaadi, coined after the idol of Lakshminarayan Dev in the central shrine. The temple is known &amp; is popular among millions of Indians because of Harikrushna Maharaj. Lord Swaminarayan was very fond of this idol &amp; advised all his devotees to worship the idol as himself. He promised to address &amp; acknowledge all the prayers with this idol.</p>
<p class="g-mb-30">The land for the temple was donated by Joban Pagi of Vadtal, who was most wanted dacoit of those times. Lord Swaminarayan converted the dacoit into his devotee years before he donated the land for the construction of temple. </p>

