<p class="g-mb-30">The temple has been a part of India’s freedom struggle. Mahatma Gandhi delivered a speech on non-cooperative movement, addressing the audience in his native language, Gujarati. He used the stage of Vadtal Swaminarayan Temple to resonate with the Hindu sentiments &amp; encourage them to join the non-cooperative movement. </p>
<p class="g-mb-30">
    Even Sardar Vallabhbhai Patel has visited Vadtal Swaminarayan Temple several times as his father, Jhaveribhai Patel, was a devotee to Lord Swaminarayan &amp; the temple.
</p>
<p class="g-mb-30">Lord Swaminarayan appointed two acharyas (religious guru) for two gaadis, Vadtal &amp; Ahmedabad. Currently, H.H 1008 Acharya Shri Rakeshprasadji Maharaj is honoring the Vadtal gaadi.</p>
